description:
## Bug Report

Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

### 1. Minimal reproduce step (Required)

On TiDB node 1:

```sql
USE test;
CREATE TABLE t1 (a INT, b INT, c INT);
CREATE TABLE t2 (a INT, b INT, c INT);
CREATE TABLE t3 (a INT, b INT, c INT);
CREATE TABLE t4 (a INT, b INT, c INT);

INSERT INTO t1 VALUES (1,3,0), (2,2,0), (3,2,0);
INSERT INTO t2 VALUES (3,3,0), (4,2,0), (5,3,0);
INSERT INTO t3 VALUES (1,2,0), (2,2,0);
INSERT INTO t4 VALUES (3,2,0), (4,2,0);

-- Wait for stats to be fully loaded
SHOW STATS_META;

CREATE INDEX idx_b ON t2(b);

SELECT t2.a, t2.b, t3.a, t3.b, t4.a, t4.b
  FROM (t3, t4)
       LEFT JOIN
       (t1, t2)
       ON t3.a = 1 AND t3.b = t2.b AND t2.b = t4.b
  ORDER BY 1, 2, 3, 4, 5;
```
2. Try executing the above SELECT statement again; it consistently reports the error: “fail to get hist meta for this histogram, possibly a deleted one”

### 2. What did you expect to see? (Required)
No errors

### 3. What did you see instead (Required)

It keeps printing the same error when executing the query.

### 4. What is your TiDB version? (Required)

v8.5.2/v8.5.1
